  }), "\n        "), "\n  "), "\n    ")), mdx("p", null, "After 4680 km I was back in Eindhoven. On the way back from Santiago de Compostela, I first went on a northern route through the Pyrenees. That was pretty hard on a touring bike with luggage. I took the train from Leon to Irun to save some time. In France, I followed the EuroVelo 1 along the coast. The route on the map Maastricht - Santiago de Compostela - Haarlem has about 5000 km. You can download the GPX file."), mdx(SevenRoutesDownload, {
