  }), "\n        "), "\n  "), "\n    ")), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "blockquote"
  }, "In Maubourguet I bought a baguette that I didn't even eat that day and 2 chocolatines that were still dripping, so fresh and hot they were. I sat down in the sun on a bench in front of a bank and was happy.", mdx("br", {
    parentName: "p"
  }), "\n", "Then to the post office. It was already half past 12 and it took a while. I bought a package with a shipping label for 6 kg for \u20AC25, bought 2 more postcards, one for mom in the package and one for Lily for her birthday. Paid with Visa. Of course, I didn't manage to finish packing the package until 12. So I had to cycle to Pau with a bulky package on my bike.", mdx("br", {
    parentName: "p"
  }), "\n", "In Pau, I navigated unerringly to the St. Jacques Church, which I didn't even know existed. It was the most beautiful day in the world. I forgot to take photos of the crowded square: fountains, people, ice cream vans.", mdx("br", {
    parentName: "p"
  }), "\n", "I packed the package. I copied the relevant Servas addresses into the route books St. James Way 1 and 2. I suddenly realized how badly sunburned I was. I had been cycling in my sleeveless jacket. My arms were crimson. My head probably too.")), mdx("p", null, "In 2008 I had no idea about how strong the sun in the south can be. My sunscreen was way too weak. I couldn't get rid of the sunburn until Santiago de Compostela. I didn't get blisters on my skin, but worried Spaniards stopped their car to tell me to use more sunscreen! My skin stayed that red for 3 weeks."), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "blockquote"
  }, "Of course, I couldn't bring my package to the post office at 6 pm on Saturday. So I went to the Christian bookstore right there and asked the woman to post my package. She was happy to do that. She had also done part of the way before.", mdx("br", {
    parentName: "p"
  }), "\n", "She even knew of an internet caf\xE9 nearby. I went there, about 4 kg lighter - felt like 10 kg! The shop was open until midnight and 5 hours would cost \u20AC8.95. I kept looking, ended up back at the church and went inside. Service was in progress. They had a friendly St. Jacques. I lit a candle for him and me. Before the mountain pass, I found that appropriate.", mdx("br", {
    parentName: "p"
  }), "\n", "Then I asked for the stamp. The one in the white robe gave me the stamp and wished me success. Ever since Nevers and Vezelage I had heard it all the time: Bom Route, Bom Chemin, Buon Camino, and in bad weather: Courage! People here were used to pilgrims.", mdx("br", {
    parentName: "p"
  }), "\n", "Then I walked to the promenade: palm trees with mountains in the background, fantastic views. At that moment, my sunburned blood circulation collapsed. I had to lie down on the next best bench. Sunstroke.", mdx("br", {
